<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-02-09T08:16:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-02-09T08:16:00-05:00" n="178" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d178">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.2300/48: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Rumania</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dennis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-02-09T15:00:00+01:44"><hi rend="italic">February 9,
                                        1924—3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 9:10
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>7. My telegram no. 5, January 22, 10 a.m.<note n="16" xml:id="d178fn16">Not printed.</note> Note received today from the Roumanian
                            Government grants all permissions requested but makes no mention of
                            aerial photography.<note n="17" xml:id="d178fn17">On June 14, 3 p.m.,
                                the Minister telegraphed that permission for aerial photography was
                                included in the note (file no. 811.2300/135).</note> Foreign Office
                            desires details of the expedition in due time.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dennis</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>